  "prompt": "How do I sync my Gmail contacts?",
  "response": "To sync your Gmail contacts across devices and platforms, you can follow these methods:\n\n1. On Android devices:\n- Go to Settings > Accounts > Google\n- Turn on contact sync\n- Select the Google account you want to sync\n\n2. On iPhone/iOS:\n- Go to Settings > Contacts > Accounts\n- Select your Google account\n- Enable \"Contacts\" toggle\n\n3. On a computer:\n- Open Gmail\n- Click \"Google Apps\" menu (9-dot grid)\n- Select \"Contacts\"\n- Click \"Export\" to backup or \"Import\" to sync from another source\n\n4. Using Google Account sync:\n- Go to contacts.google.com\n- Sign in with your Google account\n- Ensure sync is enabled in your Google Account settings\n\n5. Third-party sync tools:\n- Use apps like Google Sync\n- Use Microsoft Outlook sync feature\n- Use Mac Contacts app sync\n\n6. Additional tips:\n- Ensure you're signed into the same Google account on all devices\n- Check your internet connection\n- Update your device's software\n- Restart your device if sync fails\n\nRemember that syncing requires an active internet connection and the same Google account across devices.",
